<A HREF="#Schulte"><b>Elizabeth Schulte</b> | May Day: Haymarket and the Fight for the Eight-Hour Day</A><P>

<a name="Klein"></a><font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="4"><b>MARGARITA KLEIN</b></font><br>
<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="5"><b>Grassroots Strategies for Defending Immigrant Rights</b></font><p>

<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="2"><i>MARGARITA KLEIN is staff director for the Chicago and regional Midwest council of UNITE HERE, and a leader in the Chicago's March 10 Coalition for immigrant rights.</i><p>

<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="3">WE PUT millions of people in the streets, didn't we? All around the country, for two years in a row. And what happened? We still have all these laws in Congress that are not a solution--not even a slight solution. And the "no match" Social Security letters are a part of this.<p>

